title: WORKSHOP | Yes, you can host a house party!
description:
Why host a house party? Yes, door knocks, phone banks, rallies are all important organizing tools.  But in 2025-26, we need to do something more and different to win.  House parties can:

- Reach voters outside of our political bubbles
- Have friend and neighbor conversations with those who support our democratic values
- Inoculate voters against the onslaught of right-wing media
- Expand our volunteer base

Are you thinking about hosting a house party, but don't know how to get started?  If you've never hosted one before (and even if you're a fellow introvert), or just want a refresher, join us and the Bay Area Coalition on one of the weekly Monday, 7 pm (PT) house party workshops. You'll learn:

 - How to plan your house party
 - Tips and tools for hosting conversations with your friends, neighbors, colleagues
 - Learn PDI-on-the-GO to find your local Democrats, or others who share our values

You'll leave the workshop fired up and ready to host your house party!

title: Strategy & Tactics Working Group Meeting - Indivisible - Democracy Action Network
description:
# üì£ ANNOUNCEMENT: Strategy & Tactics Working Group - First Meeting & Reading Plan

## Who We Are
The **Strategy & Tactics Working Group** is the "brain trust" of our resistance movement, responsible for developing our strategic framework, researching effective methodologies, planning our escalation pathways, and monitoring political developments to ensure our actions have maximum impact.

## Our First Initiative: Knowledge Foundation
Before we can effectively resist, we must learn from movements that have succeeded. Our first task is building a shared knowledge foundation through strategic reading, case study analysis, and collaborative learning.

## Reading List
We'll begin with three essential texts:
- **"Blueprint for Revolution"** by Srdja Popovic
- **"This is an Uprising"** by Mark & Paul Engler
- **"Rules for Revolutionaries: How Big Organizing Can Change Everything"** by Becky Bond & Zack Exley

## Join Our First In-Person Strategy Session

**What we'll cover:**
- Facilitated discussion of "Blueprint for Revolution" and "This is an Uprising"
- Identification of key tactics and strategies relevant to our context
- Beginning our compilation of case studies
- Mapping initial power dynamics in current political landscape

**Notes:** The session will be on Zoom for those who cannot attend in person

## How to Participate Now
1. **Sign up for the reading group:**
2. **Access the readings:** Links to purchase/access all books are in the resources section
3. **Join the discussion threads:** Separate threads for each book are now open
4. **Volunteer as discussion leader:** We need facilitators for each text

title: An Afternoon with Jess Piper
description:
You're invited to An Afternoon with Jess Piper!

Since Eric Burlison, our current representative in Missouri House District 07, has made it clear that he won't participate in a legitimate, in-person town hall meeting, we're bringing you a different candidate to talk about the issues at hand.

Jess Piper is a passionate advocate for rural communities and public education in Missouri. A former high school English teacher with 16 years of experience, Piper transitioned into politics driven by her commitment to ensuring that every Missourian has a voice in the legislative process.

In 2022, she ran as a Democratic candidate for Missouri House District 01, aiming to represent a district that hadn't elected a Democrat in over three decades.

Beyond her candidacy, Piper serves as the Executive Director of Blue Missouri, an organization dedicated to supporting Democratic nominees for the Missouri state legislature. She also hosts the "Dirt Road Democrat" podcast, where she discusses issues facing rural Missourians and advocates for progressive policies.

Event will be held in the Joplin Public Library Community Room on May 31st as 2pm. All are welcome!

Brought to you by Southwest Missouri Democrats and Indivisible Joplin.

title: Unite for Veterans, Unite for America
description:
On June 6, 2025, veterans, patriots, and supporters will gather in Houston under the banner of 50501-Houston to honor the legacy of D-Day and to protest in defense of the U.S. Constitution, stand up for veterans' rights, and demand full support for those who have served.

The rally will call on the Federal Government to rehire wrongfully terminated employees and to fully fund and implement the PACT Act, a historic piece of legislation that directly affects the health and well-being of veterans exposed to toxic substances during military service.

‚ÄúThis is more than a protest‚Äîit‚Äôs a movement of accountability and unity,‚Äù organizers said. ‚ÄúWe stand for the Constitution, we stand for veterans, and we will not be silent.‚Äù

What Is the PACT Act?
The Sergeant First Class (SFC) Heath Robinson Honoring Our Promise to Address Comprehensive Toxics (PACT) Act is the most significant expansion of VA health care and benefits in decades. It ensures that veterans exposed to toxic substances‚Äîincluding burn pits, Agent Orange, and radiation‚Äîreceive the care and compensation they deserve.

Key Provisions of the PACT Act Include:

Expanded eligibility for VA health care for veterans of Vietnam, Gulf War, and post-9/11 eras

20+ new ‚Äúpresumptive conditions‚Äù linked to toxic exposure

Automatic coverage for conditions like cancers and respiratory illnesses

Required toxic exposure screenings for all enrolled veterans

Additional funding for VA research, staffing, and treatment systems

Veterans are encouraged to file claims now and check their eligibility for new or expanded benefits under this law.

Why This Matters:
Tens of thousands of veterans are affected by toxic exposures. Without full funding and government follow-through, the promises made by the PACT Act could fall short. That‚Äôs why 50501-Houston is calling on all Americans to unite on June 6‚Äîto honor those who fought for freedom and fight now for those living with the aftermath of service.
